const title = 'Tools Overview';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head><meta charset="utf-8"/><title>{title} — progrok</title><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width"/>
<style>:root{--bg:#0d1117;--fg:#c9d1d9;--accent:#58a6ff;--code-bg:#161b22}*{margin:0;box-sizing:border-box}body{font-family:system-ui,sans-serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--fg);line-height:1.6;padding:2rem;max-width:800px;margin:0 auto}nav{margin-bottom:2rem}nav a{color:var(--accent);text-decoration:none;margin-right:1rem}h1{margin-bottom:1rem;color:#fff}h2{margin:1.5rem 0 .5rem;color:#fff}p{margin:.5rem 0}pre{background:var(--code-bg);padding:1rem;border-radius:6px;overflow-x:auto;margin:1rem 0}code{font-family:monospace;font-size:.9em}table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:1rem 0}th,td{border:1px solid #30363d;padding:.5rem;text-align:left}th{background:var(--code-bg)}a{color:var(--accent)}</style>
</head>
<body>
<nav><a href="/progrok/">Home</a><a href="/progrok/docs">Docs</a></nav>
<main>
<h1>Tools Overview</h1>
<p>Server-side tools extend model capabilities without client-side implementation. Include them in the <code>tools</code> array of your chat completion request.</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Tool</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>web_search</td><td>Search the web for current information</td></tr>
<tr><td>x_search</td><td>Search posts on X (Twitter)</td></tr>
<tr><td>code_interpreter</td><td>Execute code in a sandboxed environment</td></tr>
<tr><td>collections_search</td><td>Search uploaded file collections</td></tr>
<tr><td>Remote MCP</td><td>Connect to external MCP tool servers</td></tr>
<tr><td>Function calling</td><td>Define custom functions the model can invoke</td></tr>
</table>
</main>
<footer style="margin-top:3rem;padding-top:1rem;border-top:1px solid #30363d;color:#8b949e;font-size:.85em">progrok — MIT License</footer>
</body>
</html>
